{
  "texts": [
    "Meta released public versions of LLaMA and CodeLlama, including source code, in February and August 2023 respectively.",
    "Llama is a general purpose LLM with a variety of model sizes ranging from 7 billion to 65 billion parameters [46].",
    "CodeLlama is a model more specifically trained on software and has model sizes 7B, 13B, and 34B (and, as of 29th Jan 2024, 70Bn) [41].",
    "These two freely available LLMs, LLaMA and CodeLlama, have also been used in previous work on testing topics by other researchers [34,49].",
    "Although the results presented here are based on TestGen-LLM using two internal LLMs built by Meta, the Assured LLMSE design is LLM-agnostic and allows for an arbitrary number of LLMs to each contribute test cases to the extended test class.TestGen-LLM's approach to test improvement draws inspiration from previous research on Genetic Improvement [40] and automated repair [15]."
  ]
}